starPPPLinkStatusPhysicalIndex.name: starPPPLinkStatusPhysicalIndex
starPPPLinkStatusPhysicalIndex.description: The value of ifIndex that identifies the lower-level interface over which this PPP Link is operating. This interface would usually be an HDLC or RS-232 type of interface. If there is no lower-layer interface element, or there is no ifEntry for the element, or the element can not be identified, then the value of this object is 0. For example, suppose that PPP is operating over a serial port. This would use two entries in the ifTable. The PPP could be running over `interface' number 123 and the serial port could be running over `interface' number 987. Therefore, ifSpecific.123 would contain the OBJECT IDENTIFIER ppp starPPPLinkStatusPhysicalIndex.123 would contain 987, and ifSpecific.987 would contain the OBJECT IDENTIFIER for the serial-port's media- specific MIB.

starPPPLinkStatusBadControls.name: starPPPLinkStatusBadControls

starPPPLinkStatusPacketTooLongs.name: starPPPLinkStatusPacketTooLongs
starPPPLinkStatusPacketTooLongs.description: The number of received packets that have been discarded because their length exceeded the MRU. NOTE, packets which are longer than the MRU but which are successfully received and processed are NOT included in this count.

starPPPLinkStatusBadFCSs.name: starPPPLinkStatusBadFCSs
